description:
Jazz legend Chico Hamilton (Foreststorn "Chico" Hamilton, September 20, 1921* – November 25, 2013†) has mentored generations of musicians since co-founding The New School for Jazz (http://newschool.edu/jazz) in 1986, setting them free to create their own music. In this short documentary, Chico, his students, coworkers, and friends discuss his life, his work, and his vision for the future of jazz education.

Produced by The New School, Communications and External Affairs
A Film by Oren Jacoby and Elgin Smith | http://www.storyville.org
THE NEW SCHOOL | http://www.newschool.edu
